tric function.The material in this book began as a set of lecture notes, taken by Tretkoff, of a course given by Friedrich Hirzebruch at ETH Zürich in 1996. The lecture notes were then considerably expanded by Hirzebruch and Tretkoff over a number of years. In this book, Tretkoff has expanded those notes even further, still stressing examples offered by finite covers of line arrangements. The book is largely self-contained and foundational material is introduced and explained as needed, but not treated in full detail. References to omitted material are provided for interested readers.Aimed at graduate students and researchers, this is an accessible account of a highly informative area of complex geometry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aCurves, Elliptic. 0aGeometry, Algebraic. 0aProjective planes. 0aRiemann surfaces. 0aUnit ball. 7aMATHEMATICS / Geometry / General.2bisacsh  aAppell hypergeometric function.  aChern numbers.  aEuler number.  aFriedrich Hirzebruch.  aGauss hypergeometric function.  aGaussian curvature.  aHermitian metric.  aKodaira dimension.  aMbius transformation.  aMiyaoka-Yau inequality.  aRiemann surface.  aRiemannian metric.  aalgebraic geometry.  aalgebraic surface.  aarithmetic monodromy group.  ab-space.  aball "ient.  acanonical divisor class.  acomplete quadrilateral.  acomplex 2-ball.  acomplex manifold.  acomplex surface.  acovering group.  acovering space.  adifferential geometry.  adivisor class group.  adivisor.  aelliptic curve.  afinite covering.  afirst Chern class.  afractional linear transformation.  afree 2-ball "ient.  afundamental group.  ageometry.  aintersection point.  aline arrangement.  aline bundle.  alinear arrangement.  alog-canonical divisor.  aminimal surface.  amonodromy group.  